annotations: sometimes it just feels like you are just surrounded and you just feel like youre surrounded with good love or bad love like i said this song can be interpreted so many different ways so the way i wrote it was obviously from a sense of this is not necessarily a bad situation its almost too good so im trying to make it bad to protect myself if that makes sense i think a lot of us do that in a lot of cases but it could mean anything trippin it could mean anything but for me its basically when you feel like its too good to be true and youre tryna make sure that you dont get hurt because im very definitely feel like love can feel like a drug sometimes sometimes you feel like if youre not getting back the same love that youre putting in youre withdrawn almost and you just feel like you need it and sometimes you cant put your finger on what exactly it is about it or about the person that makes you love them so much sometimes you cant understand and i think thats why sometimes people stay in bad relationships and thats why good relationships last so long it can be both sides of the spectrum definitely have been a situation where i felt like this might be too good to be true and you kind of take a backseat and its like maybe i should chill out but then again again in the sense of what the song is i come to find out that i was just making myself believe that because at the end of the day sometimes its not too good to be true sometimes it really can be a real love you knowif you go through the verse and then go through the prechorus its almost like ive created this situation in my head that somethings happening or ive put this wall up because of whats happened to me before and im kind of expecting you to do the same thing so the chorus is a moment of realization of being like wait i have to give everyone an even playing field and be like this is actually me im making something up that doesnt exist so im done trippinso this is the interesting part because everyone thinks i said its just too bitter for words but we were using a play on when you get married its actually worse when you get married you say for better or for worse right in wedding vows right so thats just too bitter for worse dont wanna taste it is as in imagine if youre getting married to someone and they say for better or for worse but were using better as bitter because this is a bitter situation so it was kind of a play on words i dont think anyone got but its fine because i love think those are actually my favorite lines of the song because especially me im a big lover like i have a lot of love to give im a very loving person and i would hate to give it to someone who doesnt deserve it or i feel like isnt really giving it back to me and yeah i think if you think about running a marathon youve put all of this training in youve put all of this working out eating well like preparing yourself for this marathon and you get to the marathon and you do k of that k and then you just collapse or something gets in your way and you no longer can do the extra k or the last k that youre supposed to do and its like all of that effort all of that preparation that youve put in to not make it to where your end goal was thats frustrating i feel like its the same in the sense of putting time and effort and loving someone to not get there in the end that just makes everything not worth it

annotations: those lyrics are kind of in that limbo place where youve broken up but someone keeps opening the door up a little bit and you come back in its all very messy and that relates to someone pushing you away as well its empty promises being made to someone when in reality something else is happening behind the scenes that you might not have seen and you just kind of find was based off those really youthful and naive promises you make the first time that you might have fallen in love its like you really do make those promises and you dont understand the depth or the actual commitment that youre speaking of the power of the words when you use them for the first time like weapons so its like for me it was something that i really didnt understand and something that ive said to someone in the past and they had said things to me as well and that lyric represents the naivety of using words that you dont fully comprehend singer puts their all into the relationship whereas their partner doesnt care this could be seen as unrequited love when the love between two people only comes from one of the pair from the lines above this also shows that the other person isnt making this separation easy and is clearing being difficult about s someone being with other people or a person behind youre back and thinking that no one can like theses schmucks cant take my place or whatever yeah i mean on a literal term its just yeah youre oblivious of what was happening behind youre back and you want to kind of know that now you know that they should kind of feel bad about it and i hope that you see my face instead of theirs or whatever which is kind of weird but you know its obviously in a dark definitely the use of the word crawl was like what it feels defeated it feels like youre coming s just that power that the person has over you and youre a puppet to them youll do whatever just to retrieve the feeling that you think is important or best for you because you dont know whats best for you i guess so its the powerlessness youre fragile and your kind of at this persons every beck and call and i think thats a lyric of frustration and s always going to be a little different for everyone in the band but youngblood for me is a way that we were living at the time were writing it and also youngblood is a person whose persona is very on and off push and give and take and all that kind of good stuff its such a visual word you can visualize the feelings of the word as well and i think that always is what connected with me about that lyric and especially how strong it strikes in the chorus as this being kind of like an allencompassing thing of what is youngblood thats what i think is so cool about the song its like even when we were playing it live the other night it didnt feel like the somber depressing moment it felt like this empowering kind of piece of music that makes you feel something and its so diverse in what it stands for and what it means and i think thats why its managed to connect the way it has because i feel like no matter how you look at it theres still some sort of relevance you can find in your life to the actual music thats happening in the prechorus feels like tension and it does feel like pushing and pulling and i think thats one of the parts that i like in this song as well the lyric binds really well with the tension that builds in the prechorus of youngbloodthose lyrics are kind of in that limbo place where youve broken up but someone keeps opening the door up a little bit and you come back in its all very messy and that relates to someone pushing you away as well its empty promises being made to someone when in reality something else is happening behind the scenes that you might not have seen and you just kind of find out

annotations: these chants may be a nod to gasoline dreams from outkasts album stankonia where andr shouts alright times in a similar is an inspiration for travis among many the two even collaborated on the ends a track from scotts previous album birds in the trap sing mcknighta reference to the overall theme of the song and the album astronomy is a science that attempts to explain phenomena that are not fully known to man for example galaxies planets and stars the concepts of both stargazing and astroworld can be linked back to this science it could also be a way for travis to explain how this current album is something that we have never seen before and do not understand therefore requiring research and reference to the bloods a gang founded in los angeles california they are primarily known for the use of their red signature color and their longstanding rivalry with the crips another gang from in this sense throwing up bs might allude to bands instead of the bshaped gang sign that the bloods lines tie back to the purpose of stargazing while it is mainly descriptive of a bad trip travis here introduces what impelled him to take the psychedelics in the first place his life has been changing quite has gained large amounts of success from his mixtape days through his massively popular debut album rodeo then birds in the trap sing mcknight and now his longawaited lp astroworld in the meantime hes gone from being a relatively unknown artist to starting a relationship with one of the worlds biggest models kylie jenner its not unlikely that for someone whose life changed so quickly travis would have wanted an escape from it all hence the impetus to segue contains similar animalistic howling heard on wolves a track off kanye wests the life of pablowolves is a deep reflection of west on his relationship with kim kardashian and she appears in the tracks music video a balmain advert scotts use of a similar sound may be an allusion to west and their shared connection to the kardashianjenner six flags corporation made the final decision to close astroworld to provide more parking spaces for when the houston texans would play at relient stadium six flags corp fell short by half of their expected earnings in selling the property making it unprofitable to relocate the amusement park since then the property has been used to host musical festivals and other events as a local artist travis likely performed at the site with childhood memories of the april kylie jenner rented out the entire california six flags theme park for a night to give travis an astroworld themed surprise party in attendance were travis and kylies friends and family including kanye travis made good on his promise to relocate and bring back astroworld to the people close to him even if it was just for one interpolates the lines from biggies mo money mo problems and drakes energy line i got enemies got a lot of enemiesby definition the word amenity could refer to a useful feature or facility of a building or place which goes along with his metaphor of living on the top floor of a building it can also refer to the pleasantness of a person travis uses a doubleentendre to describe how taxing societal expectations can bebooger sugar is a slang term for cocaine excessive use of the drug can cause your nose to term likely evolved from the pet name sugar booger a term of endearment one would call a close friend or family kicks off this line by describing his past life before fame and stardom the houston rapper spent his childhood years together with his grandmother who lived in the hood which scott elaborated on in a interview with complexi was born in houston texas i grew up in houston by missouri city its like a suburb in the area its middleclass but i used to stay with my grandma in the hood from ages one to the same interview travis explained some of the traumatizing scenes he witnessed while living in poor circumstancesgrowing up my grandmother stayed in the hood so i seen random crazy shit i saw mad bums and crazy spazzed out motherfuckers i saw people looking weird hungry and grimey i was always like i gotta get the fuck out this shit it gave me my edgeit made me who i am right now

annotations: as a devout mormon lead singer dan reynolds has run into his fair share of religious strife both with and against the church of jesus christ of latterday reynolds premiered loveloud a music festival in salt lake city utah which aims to bridge the gap between the lds church and members of the lgbtq community nearly a year later reynolds released believer a documentary about his struggles managing both his spiritual and personal to the mormon doctrine which is formed through direct consultation with god engaging in lgbtq mannerisms is a sin in the eyes of god and is considered a form of apostasy in the mormon church held a special meeting to rediscuss the issues involving homosexuality and samesex marriage but remained firm on their stancewhile the church respects the law of the land and acknowledges the right of others to think and act differently it does not perform or accept samesex marriage within its membershipafter seven happily married years together dan reynolds and aja volkman divorced since then dan has been noticeably distraught releasing heartwrenching documentary believer and a collaboration with kygo reminiscent of the couples dan realizes its time to cast out the negatives further shaping who he is in a tweet dan confirmed that to him these lines mean more than fighting heartache but rather fighting any adversity that comes his way including selfdoubt religious guilt hate and has suffered in many forms of pain his mental pain was exemplified through the entirety of the bands second album aside from mental pain dan was diagnosed with two disabling physical conditions ankylosing spondylitis as and ulcerative colitis uc additionally reynolds has not been one to shy from his spiritual pain creating the aforementioned documentary about his single plight regarding the church of jesus christ of latterday may also allude to whatever it takes message of overcoming ruin and painim just a product of the system a catastropheand yet a masterpiece and yet im halfdiseasedin a literal sense and with the end near on the horizon to make it refers to dans fortitude and making it out of the brutal landscape alive his impassioned volume of the phrases reiteration also aids this the same time these lines can also be seen as an allegory of the music industry the gruesome imagery alludes to all dan has had to do to advance in the industry despite how ruthless he may have appeared in the process

late even outside of a romantic relationship like family just telling people you love them and showing your love for anyone you love is very important because you never know it also feels good when someone says i love you or someone explains to you how they is definitely number one without trust theres no point you cant move forward i think trusting communication being honest which is again part exactly what youre searching for because i think youre too concentrated on number one number two number three number fourall these different things that perfection doesnt exist so if you go out searching for something that you have to take off all these different boxes youre not going to find someone that takes off every single box because that just doesnt exist right when you dont look for it and it just kind of comes out of nowhere and surprises you it almost feels like all those boxes are ticked anyway even if theres something at the bottom of the list that isnt it but its just again over you

annotations: as dan reynolds once said for the band weve been geeks our entire lives this meant that he might have suffered bullying in middle school since he wasnt one of the popular kids instead of a nerd who cared more about studying and to dragons are selfproclaimed nerds and would rather be labeled that than rock stars because thats who they arethey want to show that you dont have to put yourself into the spotlight to be a in this song represents the day the person achieves his dream in dans case its his musical careerhe was lightning before the thunder a person capable of achieving great things but for some reason not being able to so when he finally does the two things become one the potential in that person lightning and his dream or desired life situation thunderhes feeling that moment the along awaited thunder in his life but hes also feeling simple description of what he wants is shown here through a metaphor a young gun with a quick fuse this represents a hungry and eager person ready to take on the world and follow their own path it seems as if this person is not comfortable with their current situation which can be shown through the lyrics wanna leave my own life behindedit in the line i was uptight wanna let loose indicates that the person was uptight in life and didnt enjoy it as much as he couldve being stuck dreaming of a better situation however he realizes his mistakes and wants to let loose merging that with his idea of leaving his old life here symbolises a young and immature person one who has not reached the final climax in achieving their dreams on the other end there is thunder which is what the person later becomes this can be compared to dans life before imagine dragons first off he was just an ordinary kid like many filled with ambitions and dreams finally one day he achieves his supposed dream becoming successful in the music industry and doing what he loves in essence this line in the song takes a moment to reflect and look back at what he was before the thunder lightning can also mean someone who already has the talent and necessities to have a successful career whilst thunder is the breakout moment that is the turning point for the kids in his class laughed and made fun of him for not fitting in or being traditional the theme of verse is essentially you all doubted me and made fun of me and look at me nowthe line can also be interpreted as parallelism toward the first verse he was uptight and dreaming of being a big star while the rest of the kids around him were just having fun taking it easy laughing and not caring about their didnt conform to what he was being taught he took his own path most of the time record labels try to control what content artists release to make sure it fits the mold of popular music music in the eyes of a label isnt really about the craft anymore its about how many plays it lyric most likely could also be describing how people are told to sit and wait by taking a number and waiting for their turn to take a number is to accept that you have to wait and that youre conforming to the rules set in front of could also mean the primary objective of a ticket dispenser in some areas of work you physically take a number and wait in the space provided

the low points and highs of my life thats what believer is about and the fact that its resonating with people is really prechorus acts as the pursuit of finally letting ones pain out instead of bottling it up while the chorus is the aftermath of making it through that pain with honor and compares the act of bottling your emotions to condensation and to water flowing away from land and back again the water may be symbolical of ones body while the condensation and flowing represents the consequence behind ignoring ones instinct of feeling with sadness is fundamental to ones health when one shies away from confronting inner anguish it can result in an exaggerated sense of anxietythis is highlighted with the imagery of rain after referencing theres an escapefollowing melancholic confessions of insecurity a conclusion of breaking out of this anguish is reached with the speakers emotions overflowing and pouring out along with the rainbeliever opens with a proclamation suggesting that all the words that follow are a confession painting the rest of the songs defiant lyrics with a patina of greater hes about to say is something thats been percolating for a while this is simultaneously something thats had him intensely upset and passionate fired up and has been a longstanding problem long enough for him to be tired of itdan reynolds of imagine dragons admitted he had a rough year struggling with depression luckily a strong support system and a desire to feel better helped him see the band with clearer he was interviewed by he saidbeliever means a lot to me shaped the narrator as a person as he expresses his feelings through these very personal narrator speaks almost as if pain is a religious concept reminiscent of zen philosophy pain is viewed here as a means to spiritual ascension growth and overall happiness asserted is that without the spiritual and physical pain he went through in his place of darkness the light wouldnt have been diagnosis of both ankylosing spondylitis and ulcerative colitis unequivocally contributed to the experience of said darkness dan reynolds spoke to describing believer as a transition from a darker place to a place of lightcoming out the other side the band seems to feel more genuine and unique than ever reynolds commentedbeliever to me is the first song ive ever written in my career that i could stand back and of speaks from his mormon faith as religion gave him guidance through all the hatred he encountered mightve caused him pain it led him to contemplate on how to avoid it and be a peaceful man its only suitable he alludes to the dove a symbol of peace the bible mentions it several times notably in the table of noahs ark where the dove plucks an olive branch as a sign that the violent great flood is annotations: halseys opening line introduces an opposite to andrew taggart she takes the role of the subject in this song turning it from a monologue to a backandforth and delivering a juicy bit of insight she misses him too shes second guessing her choice of leaving him based on looks and not remembering why they broke up because she cant help but adore him for all the good last three words might be a subtle nod towards gasoline a track off of halseys debut album badlands where the first lyrics askare you insane like meshes second guessing her choice of leaving him based on looks and not remembering why they broke up because she cant help but adore him for all the good had been playing i miss you in our sets a lot at the time and blink was on our minds a lot so thats where that idea came from blink also played a large role in our musical history growing up as for tucson it just rhymed and also touches on the geographical special references we use in the just used that setting as the perfect scenario for something like this to happen commonly running into people in hotels or destinations unexpectedly it paints a very vivid image of the pretty girl at the bar with a cocktail and that sort of rush of memories and emotions mostly physical leading to a hook think its just the acknowledgement of each others flaws as people and the denial of some of them as well college and growing up at its finest selfexploration and selfrealization its less about drinking to get over and more about the lifestyle that one leads in college and sometimes after as a result in the case of the song with halsey its really a dialogue thats taking could mean a few things partially that we are stuck in time repeating a mistake of the past not learning or growing from it but it also refers to the light heartedness of this period in our song is sort of comical in nature we wanted to make a feel good song about meeting your ex falling for them on a physical level and them remembering all the horrible truths about why it didnt work out so hopefully the lyrics evoke some sort of emotional connection to people but we want people to have fun with song relates closely to the spoiled girls of college who have family money but also live this dichotomy of the broke college life for this visually range rovers and boulder communicated that the getting too specific we wanted to write a song about something personal to us but relatable to many classically there are lots of hot girls at syracuse that he would run into and find himself attracted to but forget all the things he hated about them college for us is mostly where that happened so in this case cuse thats really not relevant but enough to make a song about were listening to blinks i miss you and had just started playing it in
